  "time_ut": 1656429014,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0b89\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba8\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bae\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb3\u0bcd\u0bb3 \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Notice issued by the High Court",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The High Court today (28) announced that in view of the prevailing fuel shortage in the country and restrictions on the supply of fuel to the public, only 'urgent cases' will be taken up in open court from yesterday to July 1.",
        "The Registrar of the High Court has declared that if there are any urgent cases in the scheduled petitions or appeals or they are to be taken up in the open court, the transfer deed should be filed before the scheduled date.",
        "He also pointed out that the notice of transfer would be issued to the registered lawyers of the defendants or the opposing party.",
        "He further said that those who want to file evacuation petitions related to urgent cases should send an email to the Registrar of the High Court at least two days before the due date."
      ],
